                            <comment id="13238797" author="osiefart" created="Mon, 26 Mar 2012 20:40:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Showcase: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/osiefart/wicket-jira-bugs/tree/master/WICKET-4475&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/osiefart/wicket-jira-bugs/tree/master/WICKET-4475&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13244030" author="mgrigorov" created="Mon, 2 Apr 2012 08:27:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I updated the code to use determineVisilibility() instead of #isVisible() so visibilityAllowed() will be taken into account.&lt;br/&gt;
But it seems you didn&apos;t understand the purpose of Inline in InlineEnclosure. The markup element for the InlineEnclosure is always rendered, even if the child is invisible, this way it can be updated in Ajax requests because the placeholder tag is there.&lt;br/&gt;
If you want the markup of the enclosure to not be rendered at all then you need &amp;lt;wicket:enclosure&amp;gt;, but in this case it wont work in Ajax.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
